snippet: The number of Americans filing new applications for unemployment benefits fell last week, and confidence remains high among home builders.
abstract: Labor Dept reports new applications for unemployment benefits fell to seasonally adjusted 281,000 for week ending July 11, reversing previous week's rise; NAHB/Wells Fargo Housing Market index is reported to be 60 for July, showing that strong labor market is helping housing.
lead_paragraph: The number of Americans filing new applications for unemployment benefits fell last week, and confidence remains high among home builders.

headline.main: Jobs and Home-Building Reports Show Momentum in Economy
headline.print_headline: Jobless Claims Dip and Housing Is Steady as Economy Shows Momentum
